						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the central shrine in the Siddhanāthasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājakēsarivarmaṉ (Rājarāja I) Year: 4</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription may palaeographically be assigned to 10th Century.</p>						

						<p>It records the grant of lands of arecanut gardens as <hi rend="italic">iṟaiyili</hi> by a certain Naṭṭaṉ Peṟṟāḷ, a lady, whose native is not known, for maintaining a perpetual lamp and for the food-offerings to be made on the day of Aṉusha every month, to the deity Siddhēśvaram-uḍaiya-mahādēva of Tirunaṟaiyūr, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa</hi> in Tirunaṟaiyūr-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
